Project Planning

I strongly reccomend a two step process as you choose your topics.

1.) Generate Lots of ideas. Donât judge write them down. This means making a bunch of plots and numerical summaries, and it means reading more about the data and color.

Wait until a different day

2.) Cross of the ones that are too hard or too basic. Decide on your top 3 Start with number 1 and then make some exploratory plots to see if its acually working.

We need to convert the wk columns using pivot_longer

billboard_long <- billboard %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("wk"),
               names_to = "week",
               values_to = "rank")

We could fix the âwkâ problem with a mutate, possible using str_replace_all. Instead letâs do it directly with pivot_longer.

billboard_long <- billboard %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("wk"),
               names_to = "week",
               values_to = "rank",
               values_drop_na = TRUE,
               names_prefix = "wk")

I only want to keep the 4 songs that were on the charts the longest. To do this, Iâm going to add a column showing the total number of weeks

  group_by(track) %>% 
  mutate(weeks_charted = max(week))
